In double-blind, placebo-controlled, 12-week clinical studies of RAPAFLO, 259 (55.6%) were under 65 years of age, 207 (44.4%) patients were 65 years of age and over, while 60 (12.9%) patients were 75 years of age and over. Orthostatic hypotension was reported in 2.3% of RAPAFLO patients < 65 years of age (1.2% for placebo), 2.9% of RAPAFLO patients > 65 years of age (1.9% for placebo), and 5.0% of patients > 75 years of age (0% for placebo). There were otherwise no significant differences in safety or effectiveness between older and younger patients [
